snippet: Six were killed early Saturday in assaults believed to be retaliation for the expulsion of a major militia from the city last weekend.
abstract: Six Libyan soldiers are killed in Benghazi in overnight attacks believed to be retaliation for expulsion from city of powerful militia Libya Shield.

byline.contributor: Suliman Ali Zway and Osama al-Fitori contributed reporting.
